# By default the client uses **same-origin** requests — Vite serves HTTPS
# on :5173 and proxies every backend path (/admin, /workflows, /jobs,
# /upload, /media, /images, /download, /socket.io) to the Express server
# on http://localhost:3000. Students on machine B type
# https://<host-A-LAN-ip>:5173 and everything routes through Vite.
#
# Only override VITE_SERVER_URL if the API is on a DIFFERENT host than
# Vite (rare for dev). Setting it to "http://localhost:3000" will BREAK
# LAN access (every browser hits its own localhost) AND BREAK the webcam
# (getUserMedia refuses http:// outside loopback).
#
# Example (separate hosts, both HTTPS):
# VITE_SERVER_URL=https://api.example.com
